What is the projected market size & growth rate of the Visual Search Market?

Market Analysis and Insights

Visual Search Market

Data Bridge Market Research analyses that the digital map market will exhibit a CAGR of 17.50% for the forecast period of 2021-2028. Rising adoption of automated technologies and increasing demand for technologies that offer ease in business operations are the two major factors attributable to the growth of visual search market. This signifies that the visual search market value will rise up to USD 32,984.022 million by the year 2028.

Visual search is a type of perceptual task that typically involves an active scan of the visual environment for a particular object or feature. It is used to identify a specific predetermined target among other distractions. Visual search engines are used in a wide range of applications such as baggage scanning, security screening, electronic component manufacturing, navigation systems and others.

Rapid adoption of visual search engines in e-commerce industry is one of the major factors responsible for this unprecedented market growth. Moreover, growth and expansion of e-commerce industry will directly and positively influence the growth in demand for visual search engines. Rising demand for advanced technological solutions such as artificial intelligence and machine learning will further create lucrative and remunerative growth opportunities for the visual search market. Rising internet penetration and rising smartphone penetration will further induce growth in the demand for visual search engines.

However, high operational cost will pose a major challenge to the visual search market growth. Also, lack of skilled professionals or trained personnel will further create hindrances for the growth of visual search market. Lack of adequate technological infrastructure in low and middle class economies will further create obstacles for the visual search market.

